var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Report Builder","text":"<p>A professional C# Blazor application for generating customizable PDF reports with an intuitive web interface.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#features","title":"\u2728 Features","text":"<ul> <li>Multiple Report Support - Architecture designed for extensibility</li> <li>PDF Generation - Professional output using QuestPDF</li> <li>Customizable Sections - Toggle report sections on/off</li> <li>Dynamic Company Branding - Customize company name throughout</li> <li>Interactive UI - User-friendly Blazor interface</li> <li>PDF Import - Intelligently extract data from previous reports</li> <li>Mobile App Reports - Comprehensive iOS &amp; Android performance tracking</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#quick-start","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Quick Start","text":"First Time SetupDistribution <pre><code># 1. Install .NET 9.0 SDK\n# Download from: https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download\n\n# 2. Clone or navigate to project\ncd C:\\git\\lehman.reports\n\n# 3. Run development server\ndotnet watch run\n</code></pre> <p>App opens automatically at <code>http://localhost:5000</code></p> <pre><code># Build production package\n.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.04\"\n\n# Creates: ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip (ready to distribute)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"index.html#what-you-can-do","title":"\ud83d\udccb What You Can Do","text":""},{"location":"index.html#for-end-users","title":"For End Users","text":"<ul> <li>\u2713 Open web interface in any browser</li> <li>\u2713 Create reports with custom data</li> <li>\u2713 Import previous month's report (auto-fills old data)</li> <li>\u2713 Export configuration as JSON</li> <li>\u2713 Download PDF reports</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#for-developers","title":"For Developers","text":"<ul> <li>\u2713 Add new report types</li> <li>\u2713 Customize styling and branding</li> <li>\u2713 Extend with new features</li> <li>\u2713 Deploy to production</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#documentation-sections","title":"\ud83d\udcda Documentation Sections","text":"<ul> <li>Getting Started - Set up and first report</li> <li>Development - Architecture and code patterns</li> <li>Distribution - Build and deploy</li> <li>Reference - Configuration and API</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#technology-stack","title":"\ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Technology Stack","text":"<ul> <li>Framework: ASP.NET Core 9.0 Blazor Server</li> <li>Language: C#</li> <li>PDF: QuestPDF library</li> <li>UI: Bootstrap 5 + Blazor components</li> <li>Database: None (stateless)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#distribution","title":"\ud83d\udce6 Distribution","text":"<p>Users receive a self-contained ZIP file with: - \u2713 Complete application executable - \u2713 All dependencies included - \u2713 No installation required - \u2713 Windows batch launcher - \u2713 User documentation</p> <p>Size: 64 MB ZIP | Build Time: 2-3 minutes</p>"},{"location":"index.html#current-status","title":"\u2705 Current Status","text":"<ul> <li>Version: 1.04</li> <li>Status: Production Ready \u2713</li> <li>Last Updated: December 2025</li> </ul> <p>New here? Start with Quick Start Guide \u2192</p>"},{"location":"license.html","title":"License","text":"<p>MIT License</p> <p>Copyright (c) 2025 [Your Name/Organization]</p> <p>Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:</p> <p>The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.</p> <p>THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.</p>"},{"location":"license.html#dependencies","title":"Dependencies","text":"<p>This project uses the following open-source libraries:</p>"},{"location":"license.html#questpdf","title":"QuestPDF","text":"<ul> <li>License: Community License</li> <li>License URL: https://questpdf.com/license-summary</li> <li>Used for: PDF generation</li> </ul>"},{"location":"license.html#itext7","title":"iText7","text":"<ul> <li>License: AGPL v3</li> <li>License URL: https://github.com/itext/itext7/blob/develop/LICENSE</li> <li>Used for: PDF text extraction</li> </ul>"},{"location":"license.html#bootstrap-5","title":"Bootstrap 5","text":"<ul> <li>License: MIT</li> <li>License URL: https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/main/LICENSE</li> <li>Used for: UI framework</li> </ul>"},{"location":"license.html#net-runtime","title":".NET Runtime","text":"<ul> <li>License: MIT</li> <li>License URL: https://github.com/dotnet/runtime/blob/main/LICENSE.TXT</li> <li>Used for: Application runtime</li> </ul> <p>For complete license details, visit: https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT</p>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html","title":"Adding Features","text":"<p>Step-by-step guide to adding new features.</p>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#adding-a-new-report-type","title":"Adding a New Report Type","text":""},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#step-1-create-data-model","title":"Step 1: Create Data Model","text":"<p>Create <code>Models/MyReportConfig.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>using System.Text.Json.Serialization;\n\npublic class MyReportConfig {\n    public string AppName { get; set; } = \"\";\n    public string CreatedBy { get; set; } = \"\";\n    public DateTime ReportDate { get; set; } = DateTime.Now;\n\n    [JsonIgnore]\n    public string Version { get; set; } = \"1.04\";\n\n    public bool IsValid() {\n        return !string.IsNullOrEmpty(AppName) &amp;&amp;\n               !string.IsNullOrEmpty(CreatedBy);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#step-2-implement-generator-service","title":"Step 2: Implement Generator Service","text":"<p>Create <code>Services/MyReportGenerator.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>using QuestPDF.Fluent;\nusing QuestPDF.Helpers;\nusing QuestPDF.Infrastructure;\n\npublic class MyReportGenerator : IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt; {\n    private readonly ILogger&lt;MyReportGenerator&gt; _logger;\n\n    public MyReportGenerator(ILogger&lt;MyReportGenerator&gt; logger) {\n        _logger = logger;\n    }\n\n    public async Task&lt;byte[]&gt; GenerateAsync(MyReportConfig config) {\n        if (!config.IsValid()) {\n            throw new InvalidReportConfigException(\"Config is invalid\");\n        }\n\n        try {\n            _logger.LogInformation(\n                LogEvents.PdfGeneration, \n                \"Generating report for {AppName}\", \n                config.AppName\n            );\n\n            var document = Document.Create(container =&gt; {\n                container.Page(page =&gt; {\n                    page.Size(PageSizes.A4);\n                    page.Margin(2, PageSizes.Centimetre);\n\n                    page.Header().Text($\"Report: {config.AppName}\")\n                        .FontSize(24).Bold();\n\n                    page.Content().Column(column =&gt; {\n                        column.Item().Text($\"Created by: {config.CreatedBy}\");\n                        column.Item().Text($\"Date: {config.ReportDate:yyyy-MM-dd}\");\n                    });\n                });\n            });\n\n            var pdf = document.GeneratePdf();\n            return await Task.FromResult(pdf);\n        }\n        catch (Exception ex) {\n            _logger.LogError(\n                LogEvents.PdfGeneration, ex, \n                \"Report generation failed for {AppName}\", \n                config.AppName\n            );\n            throw new PdfException(\"Could not generate report\", ex);\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#step-3-register-service","title":"Step 3: Register Service","text":"<p>Edit <code>Program.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>// Add after other service registrations\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;\n    IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt;, \n    MyReportGenerator&gt;();\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#step-4-create-ui-component","title":"Step 4: Create UI Component","text":"<p>Create <code>Components/Pages/MyReport.razor</code>:</p> <pre><code>@page \"/myreport\"\n@inject IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt; ReportGenerator\n@inject ToastService Toast\n@inject ILogger&lt;MyReport&gt; Logger\n\n&lt;h1&gt;My Custom Report&lt;/h1&gt;\n\n&lt;form @onsubmit=\"HandleGenerateReport\"&gt;\n    &lt;div class=\"mb-3\"&gt;\n        &lt;label class=\"form-label\"&gt;App Name&lt;/label&gt;\n        &lt;input class=\"form-control\" @bind=\"Config.AppName\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n\n    &lt;div class=\"mb-3\"&gt;\n        &lt;label class=\"form-label\"&gt;Created By&lt;/label&gt;\n        &lt;input class=\"form-control\" @bind=\"Config.CreatedBy\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n\n    &lt;button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" disabled=\"@_isGenerating\"&gt;\n        @if (_isGenerating) {\n            &lt;span class=\"spinner-border spinner-border-sm me-2\"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n            Generating...\n        } else {\n            Generate PDF Report\n        }\n    &lt;/button&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n\n@code {\n    private MyReportConfig Config = new();\n    private bool _isGenerating = false;\n\n    private async Task HandleGenerateReport() {\n        if (!Config.IsValid()) {\n            Toast.ShowError(\"Please fill in all required fields\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        try {\n            _isGenerating = true;\n\n            Logger.LogInformation(\"Generating report\");\n            var pdf = await ReportGenerator.GenerateAsync(Config);\n\n            // Download file\n            await DownloadFile(pdf, \"MyReport.pdf\");\n\n            Toast.ShowSuccess(\"Report generated successfully!\");\n\n            Logger.LogInformation(\"Report generated\");\n        }\n        catch (Exception ex) {\n            Logger.LogError(ex, \"Report generation failed\");\n            Toast.ShowError($\"Error: {ex.Message}\");\n        }\n        finally {\n            _isGenerating = false;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private async Task DownloadFile(byte[] fileBytes, string filename) {\n        // See wwwroot/download.js for implementation\n        await JS.InvokeVoidAsync(\"downloadFile\", fileBytes, filename);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#step-5-add-navigation-link","title":"Step 5: Add Navigation Link","text":"<p>Edit <code>Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor</code>:</p> <pre><code>&lt;nav class=\"navbar\"&gt;\n    &lt;a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"myreport\"&gt;\n        My Custom Report\n    &lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/nav&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#adding-a-service","title":"Adding a Service","text":""},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#example-email-service","title":"Example: Email Service","text":"<p>Create <code>Services/EmailService.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>public interface IEmailService {\n    Task SendAsync(string to, string subject, string body);\n}\n\npublic class EmailService : IEmailService {\n    private readonly IConfiguration _config;\n    private readonly ILogger&lt;EmailService&gt; _logger;\n\n    public EmailService(\n        IConfiguration config,\n        ILogger&lt;EmailService&gt; logger\n    ) {\n        _config = config;\n        _logger = logger;\n    }\n\n    public async Task SendAsync(string to, string subject, string body) {\n        try {\n            _logger.LogInformation(\n                \"Sending email to {To}\", to\n            );\n\n            // Implementation here\n\n            await Task.CompletedTask;\n        }\n        catch (Exception ex) {\n            _logger.LogError(ex, \"Email send failed\");\n            throw;\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Register in <code>Program.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>builder.Services.AddScoped&lt;IEmailService, EmailService&gt;();\n</code></pre> <p>Use in components:</p> <pre><code>@inject IEmailService EmailService\n\n@code {\n    private async Task SendEmail() {\n        await EmailService.SendAsync(\n            \"user@example.com\", \n            \"Subject\", \n            \"Body\"\n        );\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#adding-configuration","title":"Adding Configuration","text":"<p>Add to <code>AppConstants.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>public static class AppConstants {\n    // Existing constants...\n\n    public static class Email {\n        public const string SmtpServer = \"smtp.gmail.com\";\n        public const int SmtpPort = 587;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use in code:</p> <pre><code>var server = AppConstants.Email.SmtpServer;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#adding-logging-events","title":"Adding Logging Events","text":"<p>Edit <code>AppConstants.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>public static class LogEvents {\n    public const int AppStartup = 1000;\n    public const int PdfGeneration = 2000;\n    public const int PdfParsing = 2001;\n    public const int FormValidation = 3000;\n    // Add your event\n    public const int EmailSent = 4000;\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use in code:</p> <pre><code>_logger.LogInformation(\n    LogEvents.EmailSent, \n    \"Email sent to {Email}\", \n    address\n);\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#testing-your-feature","title":"Testing Your Feature","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Build project <pre><code>dotnet build\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Run application <pre><code>dotnet watch run\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Navigate to your feature</p> </li> <li>Open browser</li> <li>Find link in navigation menu</li> <li> <p>Test all functionality</p> </li> <li> <p>Check logs</p> </li> <li>Open browser console (F12)</li> <li>Watch PowerShell output</li> <li> <p>Verify logging messages appear</p> </li> <li> <p>Test error cases</p> </li> <li>Try invalid input</li> <li>Test error messages</li> <li>Verify error is logged</li> </ol>"},{"location":"development/adding-features.html#deployment","title":"Deployment","text":"<p>After adding a feature:</p> <ol> <li>Test thoroughly in development</li> <li>Build release <pre><code>.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.05\"\n</code></pre></li> <li>Test in distribution</li> <li>Extract ZIP</li> <li>Run ReportBuilder.bat</li> <li>Verify feature works</li> <li>Distribute to users</li> </ol> <p>References: - Code Patterns - Architecture - Setup Guide</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html","title":"Architecture","text":"<p>Understand how the application is structured.</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#high-level-overview","title":"High-Level Overview","text":"<pre><code>\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502          User Browser                   \u2502\n\u2502  (Blazor UI + HTML/CSS/JavaScript)     \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                     \u2502 HTTP\n                     \u25bc\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502      ASP.NET Core Web Server            \u2502\n\u2502   (Blazor Server + .NET Runtime)        \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n         \u2502\n    \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n    \u25bc              \u25bc              \u25bc\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510  \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510 \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502Services\u2502  \u2502  Components \u2502 \u2502  Models  \u2502\n\u2502        \u2502  \u2502             \u2502 \u2502          \u2502\n\u2502Generate\u2502  \u2502 Pages       \u2502 \u2502 Config   \u2502\n\u2502  PDFs  \u2502  \u2502 Layout      \u2502 \u2502 Shared   \u2502\n\u2502        \u2502  \u2502 Shared      \u2502 \u2502 Data     \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518  \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518 \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#project-structure","title":"Project Structure","text":""},{"location":"development/architecture.html#components","title":"Components/","text":"<p>Contains all UI components:</p> <pre><code>Components/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Pages/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Home.razor              # Home page\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReport.razor   # Report form\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Error.razor             # Error page\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Layout/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 MainLayout.razor        # Main layout\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 NavMenu.razor           # Navigation\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Shared/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 [Reusable components]\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 App.razor                   # Root component\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Routes.razor                # URL routing\n</code></pre> <p>Technology: Blazor Server, ASP.NET Razor components</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#models","title":"Models/","text":"<p>Data structures:</p> <pre><code>Models/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReportConfig.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Report configuration data\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MonthJsonConverter.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Serialize month names\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 AppSizeJsonConverter.cs\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Format app sizes\n</code></pre> <p>Technology: C# POCOs, JSON serialization</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#services","title":"Services/","text":"<p>Business logic:</p> <pre><code>Services/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 IReportGenerator.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Interface for report creation\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReportGenerator.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 PDF generation logic\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 PdfReportParser.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 PDF import/parsing\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ToastService.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Notification service\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Exceptions.cs\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Custom exception types\n</code></pre> <p>Technology: QuestPDF, iText7, Dependency Injection</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#config","title":"Config/","text":"<p>Configuration:</p> <pre><code>Config/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.json\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Production settings\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.Development.json\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Development settings\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 .editorconfig\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Code style rules\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#wwwroot","title":"wwwroot/","text":"<p>Static assets:</p> <pre><code>wwwroot/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 lib/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Bootstrap, jQuery, etc.\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 index.html\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 app.css\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 download.js\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#data-flow","title":"Data Flow","text":""},{"location":"development/architecture.html#report-generation-flow","title":"Report Generation Flow","text":"<pre><code>1. User fills form\n           \u2193\n2. Click \"Generate PDF\"\n           \u2193\n3. Form validation\n           \u2193\n4. MobileAppReportGenerator.Generate()\n           \u2193\n5. QuestPDF creates PDF in memory\n           \u2193\n6. PDF returned to browser\n           \u2193\n7. Browser downloads file\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#pdf-import-flow","title":"PDF Import Flow","text":"<pre><code>1. User clicks \"Import PDF\"\n           \u2193\n2. Select PDF file\n           \u2193\n3. PdfReportParser.ExtractData(pdf)\n           \u2193\n4. Regex patterns find values\n           \u2193\n5. Map values to form fields\n           \u2193\n6. Form auto-fills\n           \u2193\n7. User enters new data and generates\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#dependency-injection","title":"Dependency Injection","text":"<p>Services registered in <code>Program.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>// All services registered here\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;ToastService&gt;();\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt;, \n                           MobileAppReportGenerator&gt;();\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;PdfReportParser&gt;();\n</code></pre> <p>Usage in components:</p> <pre><code>@inject IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt; ReportGenerator\n@inject ToastService Toast\n\n@code {\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync() {\n        var pdf = await ReportGenerator.GenerateAsync(config);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#request-pipeline","title":"Request Pipeline","text":"<p>How a request flows through the application:</p> <pre><code>1. Browser requests page\n           \u2193\n2. Program.cs middleware processes\n           \u2193\n3. ASP.NET Core routes to component\n           \u2193\n4. Component renders HTML\n           \u2193\n5. Blazor establishes WebSocket connection\n           \u2193\n6. User interactions sent to server\n           \u2193\n7. Event handler executes\n           \u2193\n8. Component updates\n           \u2193\n9. HTML diff sent to browser\n           \u2193\n10. Browser updates DOM\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#key-technologies","title":"Key Technologies","text":""},{"location":"development/architecture.html#blazor-server","title":"Blazor Server","text":"<ul> <li>Server-side rendering with real-time DOM updates</li> <li>WebSocket connection to browser</li> <li>C# instead of JavaScript</li> <li>Full .NET capabilities</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#questpdf","title":"QuestPDF","text":"<ul> <li>Modern PDF generation library</li> <li>Fluent API</li> <li>Professional layouts</li> <li>No external dependencies</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#itext7","title":"iText7","text":"<ul> <li>PDF text extraction</li> <li>Import previous reports</li> <li>Regex pattern matching</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#bootstrap-5","title":"Bootstrap 5","text":"<ul> <li>Responsive UI framework</li> <li>Pre-built components</li> <li>Theming support</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#configuration-management","title":"Configuration Management","text":"<p>All constants in <code>AppConstants.cs</code>:</p> <pre><code>public static class AppConstants {\n    // Server\n    public const string LocalhostUrl = \"http://localhost:5000\";\n    public const int LocalhostPort = 5000;\n\n    // Files\n    public const int MaxPdfFileSizeBytes = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB\n\n    // Logging\n    public static class LogEvents {\n        public const int AppStartup = 1000;\n        public const int PdfGeneration = 2000;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Single source of truth for configuration.</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#error-handling","title":"Error Handling","text":"<p>Three custom exceptions:</p> <pre><code>// PDF operation errors\nthrow new PdfException(\"Could not parse PDF\");\n\n// Configuration validation\nthrow new InvalidReportConfigException(\"Missing required field\");\n\n// Missing data\nthrow new MissingReportFieldException(\"Company name required\");\n</code></pre> <p>Catch specific exceptions for precise handling.</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#logging","title":"Logging","text":"<p>Structured logging throughout:</p> <pre><code>logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.AppStartup, \n    \"App started on {Url}\", AppConstants.LocalhostUrl);\n\nlogger.LogError(LogEvents.PdfGeneration, ex, \n    \"PDF generation failed for {Company}\", config.AppName);\n</code></pre> <p>Log levels: - Debug - Development only - Information - General info - Warning - Non-critical issues - Error - Errors needing attention</p>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#extending-the-architecture","title":"Extending the Architecture","text":""},{"location":"development/architecture.html#adding-a-new-report-type","title":"Adding a New Report Type","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Create Model (<code>Models/</code>)    <pre><code>public class MyReportConfig { }\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Implement Service (<code>Services/</code>)    <pre><code>public class MyReportGenerator : \n    IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt; { }\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Register in DI (<code>Program.cs</code>)    <pre><code>builder.Services.AddScoped&lt;IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt;, \n                           MyReportGenerator&gt;();\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Create Component (<code>Components/Pages/</code>)    <pre><code>@page \"/myreport\"\n@inject IReportGenerator&lt;MyReportConfig&gt; Generator\n</code></pre></p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"development/architecture.html#best-practices","title":"Best Practices","text":"<ul> <li>Keep business logic in Services</li> <li>Keep UI in Components</li> <li>Keep data in Models</li> <li>Use dependency injection</li> <li>Log important events</li> <li>Validate input data</li> <li>Use specific exceptions</li> </ul> <p>Next: Code Patterns</p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html","title":"Code Patterns","text":"<p>Common patterns used throughout the codebase.</p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#service-pattern","title":"Service Pattern","text":"<p>All business logic goes in services:</p> <pre><code>public interface IMyService {\n    Task&lt;string&gt; DoSomethingAsync(string input);\n}\n\npublic class MyService : IMyService {\n    private readonly ILogger&lt;MyService&gt; _logger;\n\n    public MyService(ILogger&lt;MyService&gt; logger) {\n        _logger = logger;\n    }\n\n    public async Task&lt;string&gt; DoSomethingAsync(string input) {\n        _logger.LogInformation(\"Processing {Input}\", input);\n        return \"Result\";\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Register in <code>Program.cs</code>: <pre><code>builder.Services.AddScoped&lt;IMyService, MyService&gt;();\n</code></pre></p> <p>Use in components: <pre><code>@inject IMyService Service\n\n@code {\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync() {\n        var result = await Service.DoSomethingAsync(\"test\");\n    }\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#configuration-pattern","title":"Configuration Pattern","text":"<p>Use <code>AppConstants.cs</code> for all constants:</p> <pre><code>public static class AppConstants {\n    public const string MyValue = \"example\";\n    public const int MyNumber = 42;\n\n    public static class Features {\n        public const bool EnableFeatureX = true;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Access anywhere: <pre><code>var value = AppConstants.MyValue;\nif (AppConstants.Features.EnableFeatureX) { }\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#exception-handling","title":"Exception Handling","text":"<p>Create specific exceptions:</p> <pre><code>public class MyException : Exception {\n    public MyException(string message) : base(message) { }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Throw with context: <pre><code>if (something_bad) {\n    throw new MyException(\"Detailed error message\");\n}\n</code></pre></p> <p>Catch specifically: <pre><code>try {\n    DoWork();\n}\ncatch (MyException ex) {\n    _logger.LogError(LogEvents.MyEvent, ex, \"Work failed\");\n    Toast.ShowError(ex.Message);\n}\ncatch (Exception ex) {\n    _logger.LogError(\"Unexpected error: {Error}\", ex.Message);\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#logging-pattern","title":"Logging Pattern","text":"<p>Always log important events:</p> <pre><code>// Initialization\n_logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.AppStartup, \"Component initialized\");\n\n// Operations\n_logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.FileProcessing, \"Processing {File}\", filename);\n\n// Errors\n_logger.LogError(LogEvents.Error, ex, \"Operation failed for {Id}\", itemId);\n\n// Debug (dev only)\n_logger.LogDebug(\"Debug info: {Value}\", value);\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#validation-pattern","title":"Validation Pattern","text":"<p>Validate input data:</p> <pre><code>public async Task&lt;Result&gt; ProcessAsync(string data) {\n    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(data)) {\n        throw new ArgumentException(\"Data is required\");\n    }\n\n    if (data.Length &gt; MaxLength) {\n        throw new ArgumentException(\"Data is too long\");\n    }\n\n    // Process...\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use in forms: <pre><code>&lt;input @bind=\"FormData.Name\" /&gt;\n\n@if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(FormData.Name)) {\n    &lt;p class=\"text-danger\"&gt;Name is required&lt;/p&gt;\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#async-pattern","title":"Async Pattern","text":"<p>Always use async for I/O operations:</p> <pre><code>// \u2713 Good - async\npublic async Task&lt;string&gt; ReadFileAsync(string path) {\n    return await File.ReadAllTextAsync(path);\n}\n\n// \u2717 Bad - blocking\npublic string ReadFile(string path) {\n    return File.ReadAllText(path);\n}\n</code></pre> <p>In components: <pre><code>@code {\n    private string _data;\n\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync() {\n        _data = await Service.GetDataAsync();\n    }\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#component-pattern","title":"Component Pattern","text":"<p>Keep components simple and focused:</p> <pre><code>@page \"/mycomponent\"\n@inject IMyService Service\n@inject ILogger&lt;MyComponent&gt; Logger\n\n&lt;h1&gt;My Component&lt;/h1&gt;\n\n@if (_isLoading) {\n    &lt;p&gt;Loading...&lt;/p&gt;\n}\nelse {\n    &lt;p&gt;@_data&lt;/p&gt;\n}\n\n@code {\n    private string _data = \"\";\n    private bool _isLoading = true;\n\n    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync() {\n        try {\n            _data = await Service.GetDataAsync();\n        }\n        catch (Exception ex) {\n            Logger.LogError(ex, \"Failed to load data\");\n        }\n        finally {\n            _isLoading = false;\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#model-pattern","title":"Model Pattern","text":"<p>Keep models simple and focused:</p> <pre><code>public class MyModel {\n    // Auto-properties\n    public string Name { get; set; } = \"\";\n    public int Value { get; set; }\n\n    // Methods for model logic\n    public bool IsValid() {\n        return !string.IsNullOrEmpty(Name) &amp;&amp; Value &gt; 0;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use in forms: <pre><code>&lt;form @onsubmit=\"HandleSubmit\"&gt;\n    &lt;input @bind=\"Model.Name\" /&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"number\" @bind=\"Model.Value\" /&gt;\n    &lt;button type=\"submit\" disabled=\"@(!Model.IsValid())\"&gt;\n        Submit\n    &lt;/button&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n\n@code {\n    private MyModel Model = new();\n\n    private async Task HandleSubmit() {\n        if (!Model.IsValid()) return;\n        await Service.SaveAsync(Model);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#dependency-injection-pattern","title":"Dependency Injection Pattern","text":"<p>Constructor injection is preferred:</p> <pre><code>public class MyService {\n    private readonly ILogger&lt;MyService&gt; _logger;\n    private readonly IConfiguration _config;\n\n    // Inject via constructor\n    public MyService(\n        ILogger&lt;MyService&gt; logger,\n        IConfiguration config\n    ) {\n        _logger = logger;\n        _config = config;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>In Blazor components, use <code>@inject</code>:</p> <pre><code>@inject IMyService Service\n@inject ILogger&lt;MyComponent&gt; Logger\n\n@code {\n    // Use injected services in code\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/code-patterns.html#error-handling-pattern","title":"Error Handling Pattern","text":"<p>Consistent error handling:</p> <pre><code>try {\n    // Do work\n}\ncatch (OperationCanceledException) {\n    // User cancelled\n    _logger.LogInformation(\"Operation cancelled\");\n}\ncatch (InvalidOperationException ex) {\n    // Expected error\n    _logger.LogWarning(ex, \"Expected error occurred\");\n    throw;\n}\ncatch (Exception ex) {\n    // Unexpected error\n    _logger.LogError(ex, \"Unexpected error\");\n    throw new ApplicationException(\"Operation failed\", ex);\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Next: Adding Features</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html","title":"Development Setup","text":"<p>Set up your development environment.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#prerequisites","title":"Prerequisites","text":"<ul> <li>.NET 9.0 SDK or later</li> <li>Git</li> <li>Code editor (VS Code, Visual Studio, or Rider)</li> <li>4GB RAM minimum</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#installation","title":"Installation","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#1-install-net-sdk","title":"1. Install .NET SDK","text":"<p>Download: dotnet.microsoft.com/download</p> <p>Choose: .NET 9.0 SDK (not just Runtime)</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#2-verify-installation","title":"2. Verify Installation","text":"<pre><code>dotnet --version\n# Output: 9.0.x or higher\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#3-clone-repository","title":"3. Clone Repository","text":"<pre><code>git clone &lt;your-repo-url&gt;\ncd lehman.reports\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#4-restore-dependencies","title":"4. Restore Dependencies","text":"<pre><code>dotnet restore\n</code></pre> <p>Downloads all NuGet packages.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#5-build-project","title":"5. Build Project","text":"<pre><code>dotnet build\n</code></pre> <p>Should complete with 0 errors.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#running-the-application","title":"Running the Application","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#recommended-watch-mode","title":"Recommended: Watch Mode","text":"<p>Auto-reloads on file changes:</p> <pre><code>dotnet watch run\n</code></pre> <p>Changes to <code>.cs</code> or <code>.razor</code> files automatically rebuild and reload the browser.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#once-off-run","title":"Once-Off Run","text":"<pre><code>dotnet run\n</code></pre> <p>Run application once. Must restart to see changes.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#ide-setup","title":"IDE Setup","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#visual-studio-2022","title":"Visual Studio 2022","text":"<ol> <li>Open <code>ReportBuilder.sln</code></li> <li>All tools included</li> <li>Press F5 to debug</li> </ol> <p>Features: - Debugger - Code completion - Hot reload - Built-in terminal</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#vs-code","title":"VS Code","text":"<ol> <li>Install extensions:</li> <li>C# Dev Kit (Microsoft)</li> <li>Blazor extension</li> <li> <p>REST Client (optional)</p> </li> <li> <p>Open folder: <code>File \u2192 Open Folder \u2192 lehman.reports</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Run: <code>dotnet watch run</code> in terminal</p> </li> </ol> <p>Features: - Code completion - Debugging - IntelliSense</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#jetbrains-rider","title":"JetBrains Rider","text":"<ol> <li>Open <code>ReportBuilder.sln</code></li> <li>All tools included</li> <li>Press Ctrl+D to debug</li> </ol> <p>Features: - Advanced refactoring - Code analysis - Hot reload</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#file-organization","title":"File Organization","text":"<pre><code>lehman.reports/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Components/          # Blazor UI components\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Pages/          # Page components (.razor)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Shared/         # Reusable components\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Layout/         # Layout components\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Models/             # Data classes\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Services/           # Business logic\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Config/             # Configuration files\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 wwwroot/            # Static assets\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Program.cs          # Application startup\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#key-files","title":"Key Files","text":"File Purpose <code>Program.cs</code> App initialization, dependency injection <code>AppConstants.cs</code> Configuration constants <code>Config/appsettings.json</code> Runtime settings <code>.editorconfig</code> Code style rules"},{"location":"development/setup.html#first-steps","title":"First Steps","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#1-run-application","title":"1. Run Application","text":"<pre><code>dotnet watch run\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#2-open-browser","title":"2. Open Browser","text":"<p>Navigate to: <code>http://localhost:5000</code></p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#3-make-a-change","title":"3. Make a Change","text":"<p>Edit <code>Components/Pages/Home.razor</code>:</p> <pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;Hello, World! \u2190 Change this text&lt;/h1&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>Save file. Browser reloads automatically (watch mode).</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#4-explore-codebase","title":"4. Explore Codebase","text":"<ul> <li><code>Components/Pages/MobileAppReport.razor</code> - Main report form</li> <li><code>Services/MobileAppReportGenerator.cs</code> - PDF generation</li> <li><code>Services/PdfReportParser.cs</code> - PDF import</li> <li><code>Models/MobileAppReportConfig.cs</code> - Data model</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#debugging","title":"Debugging","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#visual-studio-rider","title":"Visual Studio / Rider","text":"<ol> <li>Set breakpoint (click in margin)</li> <li>Press F5 to debug</li> <li>Step through code with F10/F11</li> <li>Inspect variables</li> </ol>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#vs-code_1","title":"VS Code","text":"<ol> <li>Set breakpoint</li> <li>Open debug view (Ctrl+Shift+D)</li> <li>Choose \".NET 5+ and .NET Core\"</li> <li>Press F5</li> <li>Step through code</li> </ol>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#browser-console","title":"Browser Console","text":"<p>Press <code>F12</code> to open developer tools:</p> <ul> <li>Console - See JavaScript errors</li> <li>Network - See HTTP requests</li> <li>Elements - Inspect HTML</li> </ul>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#common-tasks","title":"Common Tasks","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#run-tests","title":"Run Tests","text":"<pre><code>dotnet test\n</code></pre> <p>(Currently no tests - add with xUnit)</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#clean-build","title":"Clean Build","text":"<pre><code>dotnet clean\ndotnet build\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#build-release","title":"Build Release","text":"<pre><code>dotnet build -c Release\n</code></pre> <p>Optimized build for distribution.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#view-project-structure","title":"View Project Structure","text":"<pre><code>dotnet sln list\n</code></pre> <p>Shows all projects in solution.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#environment-variables","title":"Environment Variables","text":"<p>Development-specific settings:</p> <pre><code>// Config/appsettings.Development.json\n{\n  \"Logging\": {\n    \"LogLevel\": {\n      \"Default\": \"Debug\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Logs more details in development mode.</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":""},{"location":"development/setup.html#port-5000-in-use","title":"Port 5000 in Use","text":"<pre><code># Kill existing process\ntaskkill /F /IM dotnet.exe\n\n# Try again\ndotnet watch run\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#build-fails","title":"Build Fails","text":"<pre><code># Clean and rebuild\ndotnet clean\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#hot-reload-not-working","title":"Hot Reload Not Working","text":"<p>Restart <code>dotnet watch run</code></p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#ide-cant-find-classes","title":"IDE Can't Find Classes","text":"<p>Restart IDE - it needs to rebuild IntelliSense cache</p>"},{"location":"development/setup.html#next-steps","title":"Next Steps","text":"<ul> <li>Project architecture</li> <li>Code patterns</li> <li>Adding features</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html","title":"Build Distribution Package","text":"<p>Create a self-contained ZIP file for distributing to end users.</p>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#quick-build","title":"Quick Build","text":"<p>One command:</p> <pre><code>cd C:\\git\\lehman.reports\n.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.04\"\n</code></pre> <p>Time: 2-3 minutes Output: <code>ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip</code> (64 MB)</p>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#what-gets-built","title":"What Gets Built","text":"<p>The ZIP contains:</p> <pre><code>ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 app/                          # Executable application\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 ReportBuilder.Web.exe     # Main application\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.json          # Configuration\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.Development.json\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 [all .NET runtime files]\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ReportBuilder.bat             # Windows launcher\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Install.bat                   # Create shortcuts\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 README.md                     # User instructions\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 INSTALLATION.txt              # Setup guide\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#build-process","title":"Build Process","text":"<p>The script automatically:</p> <ol> <li>\u2713 Checks .NET is installed</li> <li>\u2713 Cleans previous builds</li> <li>\u2713 Restores NuGet packages</li> <li>\u2713 Builds in Release mode</li> <li>\u2713 Publishes self-contained app</li> <li>\u2713 Copies to distribution folder</li> <li>\u2713 Creates ZIP archive</li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#updating-version","title":"Updating Version","text":"<p>Before each build, update the version:</p> <pre><code># 1. Update in code\n# Models/MobileAppReportConfig.cs\npublic string Version { get; set; } = \"1.05\";\n\n# 2. Build with new version\n.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.05\"\n</code></pre> <p>Creates: <code>ReportBuilder-v1.05.zip</code></p>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#verification","title":"Verification","text":"<p>After building, verify the package:</p> <pre><code># 1. Extract ZIP\nExpand-Archive ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip -DestinationPath test-extract\\\n\n# 2. Run the app\n.\\test-extract\\ReportBuilder\\app\\ReportBuilder.Web.exe\n\n# 3. Wait 10 seconds and navigate to http://localhost:5000\n\n# 4. Test all features\n#    - Create a report\n#    - Import a PDF\n#    - Export JSON config\n\n# 5. Delete test folder\nRemove-Item test-extract -Recurse\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#distribution-methods","title":"Distribution Methods","text":""},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#email","title":"Email","text":"<p>Attach or link the ZIP:</p> <pre><code>Subject: Report Builder v1.04 - Download\n\nHi Team,\n\nNew version of Report Builder is available.\n\nDownload: ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip (64 MB)\n\nInstructions:\n1. Download and extract ZIP\n2. Run ReportBuilder.bat\n3. App opens in browser\n\nNo installation needed!\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#cloud-storage","title":"Cloud Storage","text":"<p>Upload to shared location:</p> <ul> <li>OneDrive: Share link with download permissions</li> <li>Google Drive: Upload and share</li> <li>Dropbox: Upload and get shareable link</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#github-release","title":"GitHub Release","text":"<pre><code># 1. Navigate to your repo\n# 2. GitHub \u2192 Releases \u2192 Create new release\n\n# 3. Upload ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip\n# 4. Add release notes\n# 5. Publish\n\n# Users download from: github.com/your-repo/releases\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#website-hosting","title":"Website Hosting","text":"<p>Upload ZIP to your web server:</p> <pre><code>https://your-domain.com/downloads/ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip\n</code></pre> <p>Share the download link.</p>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#user-instructions","title":"User Instructions","text":"<p>Provide users with:</p> <pre><code>REPORT BUILDER v1.04 - USER INSTRUCTIONS\n\n1. DOWNLOAD\n   Download ReportBuilder-v1.04.zip\n\n2. EXTRACT\n   Right-click ZIP \u2192 Extract All\n   Choose a folder\n\n3. RUN\n   Double-click ReportBuilder.bat\n   Wait 10 seconds for browser to open\n\n4. USE\n   Fill out report form\n   Click \"Generate PDF Report\"\n   Download your PDF\n\nSYSTEM REQUIREMENTS:\n- Windows 10+ (or macOS/Linux)\n- No installation required\n- All dependencies included\n\nTROUBLESHOOTING:\nPort 5000 in use?\n  \u2192 Edit: app\\appsettings.json\n  \u2192 Change port number\n  \u2192 Restart app\n\nBrowser won't connect?\n  \u2192 Wait 15 seconds and refresh\n  \u2192 Check Windows Firewall\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#troubleshooting-build","title":"Troubleshooting Build","text":""},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#build-fails","title":"Build Fails","text":"<pre><code># 1. Clean everything\ndotnet clean\nRemove-Item -Recurse -Force bin, obj, publish\n\n# 2. Restore packages\ndotnet restore\n\n# 3. Try build again\n.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.04\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#executable-too-large","title":"Executable Too Large","text":"<p>Normal for self-contained .NET: - Runtime: 50 MB - Application: 14 MB - Total: ~64 MB</p>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#missing-files-in-zip","title":"Missing Files in ZIP","text":"<p>Verify the build:</p> <pre><code># Check dist\\app folder\nGet-ChildItem dist\\app -Recurse | Measure-Object\n\n# Should have 100+ files\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#version-numbering","title":"Version Numbering","text":"<p>Suggested versioning:</p> <pre><code>1.00 - Initial release\n1.01 - Bug fixes\n1.02 - Bug fixes\n1.03 - Bug fixes\n1.04 - Current version\n\n2.00 - Major feature release\n2.01 - Fixes for v2.0\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"guides/build-distribution.html#next-steps","title":"Next Steps","text":"<ul> <li>Deploy to users</li> <li>Update application</li> <li>Monitor usage</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html","title":"First Report","text":"<p>Walk through creating your first Mobile App Store Performance report.</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-1-open-the-application","title":"Step 1: Open the Application","text":"<ol> <li>Run: <code>dotnet watch run</code> (development) or <code>ReportBuilder.bat</code> (distribution)</li> <li>Wait for browser to open</li> <li>Navigate to <code>http://localhost:5000</code> if it doesn't open automatically</li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-2-navigate-to-reports","title":"Step 2: Navigate to Reports","text":"<p>Click \"Mobile App Store Performance Report\" in the navigation menu.</p> <p>You'll see a form with several sections:</p> <ul> <li>General Information</li> <li>Report Display Options</li> <li>iOS Platform Metrics</li> <li>Download Sources</li> <li>Android Platform Metrics</li> <li>Platform Comparison</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-3-fill-general-information","title":"Step 3: Fill General Information","text":"Field Example Company Name My App Company Report Month December 2025 Previous Month November 2025 Creator Name Jane Doe Creator Title Analytics Manager"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-4-choose-report-sections","title":"Step 4: Choose Report Sections","text":"<p>Toggle which sections to include:</p> <ul> <li>\u2713 iOS Platform Metrics (recommended)</li> <li>\u2713 Download Sources (recommended)</li> <li>\u2713 Android Platform Metrics</li> <li>\u2713 Platform Comparison</li> </ul> <p>Only enabled sections appear in the PDF.</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-5-fill-ios-metrics","title":"Step 5: Fill iOS Metrics","text":"<p>For each metric, enter:</p> Column Meaning Current Period This month's value Last Period Previous month's value % Change Percentage difference <p>Example: - Total Downloads (Current): 150,000 - Total Downloads (Last): 120,000 - % Change: +25%</p> <p>Metrics include: - Total Downloads - Active Users (30-day) - Crash-Free Users % - App Size (MB) - And more...</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-6-add-download-sources","title":"Step 6: Add Download Sources","text":"<p>Click \"Add Download Source\" to add sources:</p> <ol> <li>Enter source name (e.g., \"App Store Organic\")</li> <li>Enter metrics for that source</li> <li>Click \"Add\"</li> <li>Repeat for other sources</li> </ol> <p>Example sources: - App Store Organic Search - App Store Browse - Web Referral - Social Media - Direct Install</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-7-fill-android-metrics","title":"Step 7: Fill Android Metrics","text":"<p>Same format as iOS - enter current, previous, and % change.</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-8-platform-comparison","title":"Step 8: Platform Comparison","text":"<p>Compare iOS vs Android across categories:</p> <ul> <li>User Metrics</li> <li>Engagement</li> <li>Technical Performance</li> <li>Market Share</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#step-9-generate-report","title":"Step 9: Generate Report","text":"<ol> <li>Review all entered data</li> <li>Click \"Generate PDF Report\" button</li> <li>Browser downloads <code>MobileAppReport.pdf</code></li> <li>Open and verify the PDF</li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#using-pdf-import-faster-next-time","title":"Using PDF Import (Faster Next Time)","text":"<p>For next month's report:</p> <ol> <li>Click \"\ud83d\udcc2 Import Last Month's PDF\"</li> <li>Select the PDF you just created</li> <li>The form auto-fills with last month's data</li> <li>Just enter new \"Current Period\" values</li> <li>Click Generate</li> </ol> <p>This cuts data entry time by ~50%!</p>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#exporting-your-config","title":"Exporting Your Config","text":"<p>To save your form data:</p> <ol> <li>Click \"\ud83d\udcbe Export Config (JSON)\"</li> <li>Browser downloads <code>report-config.json</code></li> <li>Keep for backup or team sharing</li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#tips-tricks","title":"Tips &amp; Tricks","text":""},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#validating-data","title":"Validating Data","text":"<ul> <li>All fields are validated before generation</li> <li>Red error messages show what needs fixing</li> <li>Cannot generate with invalid data</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#batch-operations","title":"Batch Operations","text":"<ul> <li>Export one report's JSON</li> <li>Use it as template for next month</li> <li>Just change the values and reuse</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"<ul> <li>PDF won't generate? Check browser console (F12)</li> <li>Missing data? Check for red error messages</li> <li>Wrong values? Use browser's back button to check fields</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/first-report.html#next-steps","title":"Next Steps","text":"<ul> <li>Build for distribution</li> <li>Learn the architecture</li> <li>Advanced customization</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html","title":"Getting Started","text":"<p>Get up and running in minutes.</p>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#for-developers","title":"For Developers","text":""},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#prerequisites","title":"Prerequisites","text":"<ul> <li>.NET 9.0 SDK - Download</li> <li>A code editor (VS Code, Visual Studio, etc.)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#setup","title":"Setup","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Verify .NET Installation <pre><code>dotnet --version  # Should show 9.0.x or higher\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Clone Repository <pre><code>git clone &lt;repo-url&gt;\ncd lehman.reports\n</code></pre></p> </li> <li> <p>Restore &amp; Run <pre><code>dotnet watch run\n</code></pre>    App launches at <code>http://localhost:5000</code> with auto-reload.</p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"<p>Port 5000 in use? <pre><code>taskkill /F /IM dotnet.exe\ndotnet watch run\n</code></pre></p> <p>Connection refused? - Wait 10-15 seconds for startup - Refresh browser - Check PowerShell for errors</p> <p>Large first build? - Normal - .NET is downloading dependencies - Takes 2-3 minutes first time only</p>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#for-end-users","title":"For End Users","text":""},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#prerequisites_1","title":"Prerequisites","text":"<ul> <li>Windows 10+ (or macOS/Linux)</li> <li>~500 MB free disk space</li> <li>Any modern web browser</li> </ul>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#installation","title":"Installation","text":"<ol> <li>Download <code>ReportBuilder-v1.05.zip</code></li> <li>Extract - Right-click ZIP \u2192 Extract All</li> <li>Run - Double-click <code>ReportBuilder.bat</code> in the extracted folder</li> <li>Wait - 10 seconds for app to start</li> <li>Browser opens automatically to the application</li> </ol> <p>That's it! No installation required.</p>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#system-requirements","title":"System Requirements","text":"<p>Minimum: - Windows 10 / macOS 10.14+ / Ubuntu 18.04+ - 4 GB RAM - Modern browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari)</p> <p>Recommended: - Windows 11 / macOS 12+ / Ubuntu 22.04+ - 8 GB RAM - Latest browser version</p>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#port-already-in-use","title":"Port Already in Use?","text":"<p>If you get \"address already in use\" error:</p> <ol> <li>Open <code>appsettings.json</code> (in the extracted folder)</li> <li>Find: <code>\"localhost:5000\"</code></li> <li>Change to: <code>\"localhost:5001\"</code></li> <li>Save and re-run <code>ReportBuilder.bat</code></li> </ol>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#uninstall","title":"Uninstall","text":"<p>Just delete the extracted folder. No registry entries or leftover files.</p>"},{"location":"guides/quick-start.html#next-steps","title":"Next Steps","text":"<ul> <li>Creating Your First Report</li> <li>Building a Distribution</li> <li>View Full Documentation</li> </ul>"},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html","title":"API Reference","text":"<p>Key classes and methods.</p>"},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#services","title":"Services","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#ireportgenerator","title":"IReportGenerator <p>Interface for generating reports.</p> <pre><code>public interface IReportGenerator&lt;TConfig&gt; {\n    Task&lt;byte[]&gt; GenerateAsync(TConfig config);\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Type Parameter: Configuration class for the report</p> <p>Returns: PDF file as byte array</p> <p>Example: <pre><code>@inject IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt; ReportGenerator\n\nvar pdf = await ReportGenerator.GenerateAsync(config);\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#mobileappreportgenerator","title":"MobileAppReportGenerator <p>Generates mobile app performance reports.</p> <p>Implements: <code>IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt;</code></p> <p>Methods: <pre><code>public async Task&lt;byte[]&gt; GenerateAsync(MobileAppReportConfig config)\n</code></pre></p> <p>Features: - iOS metrics - Android metrics - Download sources - Platform comparison - Professional PDF layout</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#pdfreportparser","title":"PdfReportParser <p>Extracts data from PDF files.</p> <pre><code>public class PdfReportParser {\n    public async Task&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt; ExtractDataAsync(Stream pdfStream)\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Parameters: - <code>pdfStream</code> - PDF file as stream</p> <p>Returns: Parsed configuration object</p> <p>Throws: <code>PdfException</code> if parsing fails</p> <p>Example: <pre><code>var config = await parser.ExtractDataAsync(pdfStream);\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#toastservice","title":"ToastService <p>Displays notifications to user.</p> <pre><code>public class ToastService {\n    public void ShowSuccess(string message)\n    public void ShowError(string message)\n    public void ShowWarning(string message)\n    public void ShowInfo(string message)\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Usage: <pre><code>@inject ToastService Toast\n\n@code {\n    protected override void OnInitialized() {\n        Toast.ShowSuccess(\"Loaded successfully!\");\n    }\n}\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#models","title":"Models","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#mobileappreportconfig","title":"MobileAppReportConfig <p>Configuration for mobile app report.</p> <pre><code>public class MobileAppReportConfig {\n    // General\n    public string AppName { get; set; }\n    public string CreatedBy { get; set; }\n    public string CreatorTitle { get; set; }\n    public Month ReportMonth { get; set; }\n    public Month PreviousMonth { get; set; }\n    public string Version { get; set; }\n\n    // Section toggles\n    public bool IncludeIosMetrics { get; set; }\n    public bool IncludeAndroidMetrics { get; set; }\n    public bool IncludeDownloadSources { get; set; }\n    public bool IncludePlatformComparison { get; set; }\n    public bool IncludeTechnicalSpecs { get; set; }\n\n    // iOS metrics\n    public decimal IosCurrentDownloads { get; set; }\n    public decimal IosPreviousDownloads { get; set; }\n    public decimal IosDownloadsChangePercent { get; set; }\n\n    // More fields...\n\n    // Validation\n    public bool IsValid() { }\n}\n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#month","title":"Month <p>Enum for months.</p> <pre><code>public enum Month {\n    January = 1,\n    February = 2,\n    // ... through December = 12\n}\n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#exceptions","title":"Exceptions","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#pdfexception","title":"PdfException <p>Thrown when PDF operation fails.</p> <pre><code>public class PdfException : Exception {\n    public PdfException(string message) : base(message) { }\n    public PdfException(string message, Exception inner) \n        : base(message, inner) { }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Thrown by: - <code>MobileAppReportGenerator.GenerateAsync()</code> - <code>PdfReportParser.ExtractDataAsync()</code></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#invalidreportconfigexception","title":"InvalidReportConfigException <p>Thrown when configuration is invalid.</p> <pre><code>public class InvalidReportConfigException : Exception {\n    public InvalidReportConfigException(string message) \n        : base(message) { }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Thrown by: - Any validation check</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#missingreportfieldexception","title":"MissingReportFieldException <p>Thrown when required field is missing.</p> <pre><code>public class MissingReportFieldException : Exception {\n    public MissingReportFieldException(string fieldName) \n        : base($\"Missing required field: {fieldName}\") { }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Thrown by: - Data extraction logic</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#components","title":"Components","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#mobileappreportrazor","title":"MobileAppReport.razor <p>Main report form.</p> <p>Parameters: None</p> <p>Events: - Form submission triggers PDF generation</p> <p>Usage: <pre><code>Navigate to: /report\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#homerazor","title":"Home.razor <p>Home page with feature overview.</p> <p>Parameters: None</p> <p>Navigation: - Links to reports - Quick start info</p> <p>Usage: <pre><code>Navigate to: /\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#navmenurazor","title":"NavMenu.razor <p>Navigation menu component.</p> <p>Shows: Links to all reports and pages</p> <p>Reusable: Yes, included in MainLayout</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#constants","title":"Constants","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#appconstants","title":"AppConstants <p>Central configuration class.</p> <pre><code>public static class AppConstants {\n    public const string LocalhostUrl = \"http://localhost:5000\";\n    public const int LocalhostPort = 5000;\n\n    public const int MaxPdfFileSizeBytes = 10 * 1024 * 1024;\n\n    public const string AppVersion = \"1.04\";\n\n    public static class LogEvents {\n        public const int AppStartup = 1000;\n        public const int PdfGeneration = 2000;\n        // ... more events\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Access: <pre><code>var url = AppConstants.LocalhostUrl;\n_logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.AppStartup, \"Started\");\n</code></pre></p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#dependency-injection","title":"Dependency Injection","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#registered-services","title":"Registered Services <pre><code>// In Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;ToastService&gt;();\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;\n    IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt;, \n    MobileAppReportGenerator&gt;();\nbuilder.Services.AddScoped&lt;PdfReportParser&gt;();\n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#lifetimes","title":"Lifetimes <ul> <li>Scoped: One per request/connection</li> <li>Transient: New instance every time</li> <li>Singleton: One for entire application</li> </ul> <p>Most services are Scoped.</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#json-serialization","title":"JSON Serialization","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#monthjsonconverter","title":"MonthJsonConverter <p>Converts Month enum to/from string.</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"ReportMonth\": \"December\",\n  \"PreviousMonth\": \"November\"\n}\n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#appsizejsonconverter","title":"AppSizeJsonConverter <p>Converts app size to/from GB/MB format.</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"AppSize\": \"250 MB\",\n  \"PreviousAppSize\": \"230 MB\"\n}\n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#logging-events","title":"Logging Events","text":"<pre><code>public static class LogEvents {\n    public const int AppStartup = 1000;\n    public const int PdfGeneration = 2000;\n    public const int PdfParsing = 2001;\n    public const int FormValidation = 3000;\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Usage: <pre><code>_logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.PdfGeneration, \"Generating PDF\");\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#http-endpoints","title":"HTTP Endpoints","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#built-in-endpoints","title":"Built-in Endpoints    Endpoint Purpose     <code>/</code> Home page   <code>/report</code> Mobile app report form   <code>/_framework/...</code> Blazor framework files   <code>/lib/...</code> Static libraries (Bootstrap, etc.)","text":""},{"location":"reference/api-reference.html#no-rest-api","title":"No REST API <p>This is a Blazor Server app (not API).</p> <p>For REST API, create separate ASP.NET Core API project.</p>  <p>See Also: - Code Patterns - Architecture</p>","text":""},{"location":"reference/configuration.html","title":"Configuration Reference","text":"<p>All configurable settings and constants.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#appconstantscs","title":"AppConstants.cs","text":"<p>Central configuration file in root directory.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#server-settings","title":"Server Settings","text":"<pre><code>public const string LocalhostUrl = \"http://localhost:5000\";\npublic const int LocalhostPort = 5000;\n</code></pre> <p>Change these to use a different port or protocol.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#file-limits","title":"File Limits","text":"<pre><code>public const int MaxPdfFileSizeBytes = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB\n</code></pre> <p>Maximum file size for PDF imports.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#application-metadata","title":"Application Metadata","text":"<pre><code>public const string AppName = \"Report Builder\";\npublic const string AppVersion = \"1.04\";\n</code></pre> <p>Update <code>AppVersion</code> before each release.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#logging-events","title":"Logging Events","text":"<pre><code>public static class LogEvents {\n    public const int AppStartup = 1000;\n    public const int PdfGeneration = 2000;\n    public const int PdfParsing = 2001;\n    public const int FormValidation = 3000;\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use these when logging important events.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#appsettingsjson","title":"appsettings.json","text":"<p>Runtime configuration in <code>Config/</code> folder.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#logging","title":"Logging","text":"<pre><code>{\n  \"Logging\": {\n    \"LogLevel\": {\n      \"Default\": \"Information\",\n      \"Microsoft\": \"Warning\",\n      \"System\": \"Warning\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Log levels: - <code>Debug</code> - Very detailed (dev only) - <code>Information</code> - General info - <code>Warning</code> - Non-critical issues - <code>Error</code> - Errors - <code>Critical</code> - App-breaking errors</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#server","title":"Server","text":"<pre><code>{\n  \"Urls\": \"http://localhost:5000\",\n  \"AllowedHosts\": \"*\"\n}\n</code></pre> <ul> <li><code>Urls</code> - Where to listen</li> <li><code>AllowedHosts</code> - Allowed host headers (* = any)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#questpdf","title":"QuestPDF","text":"<pre><code>{\n  \"QuestPDF\": {\n    \"ProxyUsage\": \"Environment\"\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>QuestPDF license management.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#appsettingsdevelopmentjson","title":"appsettings.Development.json","text":"<p>Development-specific overrides (in <code>Config/</code> folder).</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"Logging\": {\n    \"LogLevel\": {\n      \"Default\": \"Debug\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>More verbose logging in development.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#editorconfig","title":".editorconfig","text":"<p>Code style rules (in <code>Config/</code> folder).</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#indentation","title":"Indentation","text":"<pre><code>[*.cs]\nindent_style = space\nindent_size = 4\n</code></pre> <p>Use 4-space indentation.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#naming-conventions","title":"Naming Conventions","text":"<pre><code># Public types: PascalCase\ndotnet_naming_rule.public_types_must_be_pascal_case.symbols = public_symbols\ndotnet_naming_symbols.public_symbols.applicable_kinds = class,struct,interface,enum\ndotnet_naming_symbols.public_symbols.applicable_accessibilities = public\ndotnet_naming_symbols.public_symbols.required_modifiers = \ndotnet_naming_style.pascal_case_style.capitalization = pascal_case\n\n# Private fields: _camelCase\ndotnet_naming_rule.private_fields_must_be_camel_case.symbols = private_symbols\ndotnet_naming_symbols.private_symbols.applicable_kinds = field\ndotnet_naming_symbols.private_symbols.applicable_accessibilities = private\ndotnet_naming_style.camel_case_style.capitalization = camel_case\ndotnet_naming_style.camel_case_style.required_prefix = _\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#port-configuration","title":"Port Configuration","text":""},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#default-port","title":"Default Port","text":"<pre><code>http://localhost:5000\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#change-port","title":"Change Port","text":"<p>Option 1: Environment Variable (best for distribution)</p> <pre><code>$env:ASPNETCORE_URLS = \"http://localhost:5001\"\ndotnet run\n</code></pre> <p>Option 2: Edit appsettings.json</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"Urls\": \"http://localhost:5001\"\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Option 3: Edit AppConstants.cs</p> <pre><code>public const string LocalhostUrl = \"http://localhost:5001\";\npublic const int LocalhostPort = 5001;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#for-distribution-users","title":"For Distribution Users","text":"<p>Edit <code>dist/app/appsettings.json</code>:</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"Urls\": \"http://localhost:5001\"\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Then restart <code>ReportBuilder.bat</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#database-configuration","title":"Database Configuration","text":"<p>Not applicable - this app is stateless.</p> <p>No database is used. All data is: - Received from user input - Processed in memory - Returned as PDF - Not stored anywhere</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#authentication","title":"Authentication","text":"<p>Not implemented - open application.</p> <p>This app has no login or authentication. If you need it:</p> <ol> <li>Install ASP.NET Core Authentication</li> <li>Add identity provider (Azure AD, Google, etc.)</li> <li>Protect routes with <code>[Authorize]</code></li> <li>Add login/logout UI</li> </ol>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#cors-configuration","title":"CORS Configuration","text":"<p>Not needed - single-domain app.</p> <p>Currently allows all origins. If you need CORS:</p> <pre><code>// In Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddCors(options =&gt; {\n    options.AddPolicy(\"AllowSpecific\", policy =&gt; {\n        policy\n            .WithOrigins(\"https://example.com\")\n            .AllowAnyMethod()\n            .AllowAnyHeader();\n    });\n});\n\napp.UseCors(\"AllowSpecific\");\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#feature-flags","title":"Feature Flags","text":"<p>Not implemented but easy to add:</p> <pre><code>public static class Features {\n    public const bool EnableEmailExport = false;\n    public const bool EnableDatabaseStorage = false;\n    public const bool EnableUserAuth = false;\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Use in code:</p> <pre><code>if (Features.EnableEmailExport) {\n    // Show email export button\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#environment-variables","title":"Environment Variables","text":""},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#development","title":"Development","text":"<p>Set in Visual Studio Properties or <code>launchSettings.json</code>:</p> <pre><code>{\n  \"ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT\": \"Development\",\n  \"ASPNETCORE_URLS\": \"http://localhost:5000\"\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#production","title":"Production","text":"<p>Set via system environment or deployment platform:</p> <pre><code>$env:ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT = \"Production\"\n$env:ASPNETCORE_URLS = \"http://0.0.0.0:80\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#version-management","title":"Version Management","text":"<p>Update version in multiple places:</p> <p>1. AppConstants.cs <pre><code>public const string AppVersion = \"1.05\";\n</code></pre></p> <p>2. Models/MobileAppReportConfig.cs <pre><code>public string Version { get; set; } = \"1.05\";\n</code></pre></p> <p>3. Build Distribution <pre><code>.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.05\"\n</code></pre></p> <p>4. Documentation (optional) <pre><code># Version 1.05\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#logging-configuration","title":"Logging Configuration","text":""},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#log-levels","title":"Log Levels","text":"Level Use Case <code>Debug</code> Detailed development info (dev only) <code>Information</code> General app flow and important events <code>Warning</code> Recoverable issues <code>Error</code> Errors that need attention <code>Critical</code> App-breaking errors"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#log-categories","title":"Log Categories","text":"<p>Organize logs by area:</p> <pre><code>// Per-class logging\nprivate readonly ILogger&lt;MyClass&gt; _logger;\n\n// Log specific events\n_logger.LogInformation(LogEvents.MyEvent, \"Message: {Value}\", value);\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#view-logs","title":"View Logs","text":"<p>Development: - Console output - IDE debug window - Browser console (F12)</p> <p>Production: - File logging (add sink) - Cloud logging (Azure, DataDog, etc.) - Event Viewer</p>"},{"location":"reference/configuration.html#secrets-management","title":"Secrets Management","text":"<p>Development: Use <code>appsettings.Development.json</code></p> <pre><code>{\n  \"ApiKey\": \"dev-key-12345\"\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Production: Use environment variables</p> <pre><code>$env:ApiKey = \"prod-key-xxxxx\"\n</code></pre> <p>Never commit secrets to git!</p> <p>See Also: - Quick Start - Development Setup</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html","title":"FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions","text":"<p>Common questions and answers.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#installation-setup","title":"Installation &amp; Setup","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-do-i-need-net-installed-to-run-the-app","title":"Q: Do I need .NET installed to run the app?","text":"<p>A: Only for development. Users receiving the distribution ZIP don't need .NET - everything is included.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-run-this-on-macos-or-linux","title":"Q: Can I run this on macOS or Linux?","text":"<p>A: Yes! The code is cross-platform. Just install .NET 9.0 SDK and run <code>dotnet watch run</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-much-disk-space-do-i-need","title":"Q: How much disk space do I need?","text":"<p>A: - Development: ~500 MB - Distribution: ~64 MB (ZIP) - Extracted: ~200 MB</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-install-multiple-versions","title":"Q: Can I install multiple versions?","text":"<p>A: Yes, extract to different folders or use different ports in <code>appsettings.json</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#usage","title":"Usage","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-import-a-previous-months-report","title":"Q: How do I import a previous month's report?","text":"<p>A: 1. Click \"Import Last Month's PDF\" 2. Select your previous month's PDF file 3. Form auto-fills with old data 4. Enter new current period values 5. Generate PDF</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-export-my-form-data","title":"Q: Can I export my form data?","text":"<p>A: Yes, click \"Export Config (JSON)\" to download your form values as JSON file.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-import-a-json-config","title":"Q: Can I import a JSON config?","text":"<p>A: Currently, JSON export is for backup only. Manual import coming in future version.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-what-report-formats-are-supported","title":"Q: What report formats are supported?","text":"<p>A: Currently PDFs generated from this app. Importing works best with PDFs from this app.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-customize-the-report-layout","title":"Q: Can I customize the report layout?","text":"<p>A: Yes, edit <code>Services/MobileAppReportGenerator.cs</code> and modify the QuestPDF layout code.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#technical","title":"Technical","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-where-is-my-data-stored","title":"Q: Where is my data stored?","text":"<p>A: Nowhere! All processing happens in memory. No database, no cloud storage, no logs of your data.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-is-the-application-secure","title":"Q: Is the application secure?","text":"<p>A:  - No authentication required - No data transmission to external servers - All processing happens locally - PDFs are generated in memory</p> <p>If you need security (auth, encryption), add it yourself.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-what-if-the-pdf-import-fails","title":"Q: What if the PDF import fails?","text":"<p>A: - Manual entry (just fill the form) - Use JSON export from previous month as reference - Contact support if pattern matching fails</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-big-can-pdf-files-be","title":"Q: How big can PDF files be?","text":"<p>A: Maximum 10 MB (configurable in <code>AppConstants.cs</code>).</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-use-this-on-a-web-server","title":"Q: Can I use this on a web server?","text":"<p>A: Yes, but requires modification: 1. Change <code>localhost:5000</code> to your server URL 2. Add authentication if exposed publicly 3. Add HTTPS configuration 4. Deploy to Windows Server or Azure</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-automate-report-generation","title":"Q: Can I automate report generation?","text":"<p>A: Yes, create a service that: 1. Calls <code>IReportGenerator&lt;MobileAppReportConfig&gt;</code> 2. Passes configuration 3. Saves PDF to file</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#development","title":"Development","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-add-a-new-report-type","title":"Q: How do I add a new report type?","text":"<p>A: See Adding Features - step-by-step guide.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-add-a-database","title":"Q: How do I add a database?","text":"<p>A: 1. Install Entity Framework: <code>dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore</code> 2. Create DbContext class 3. Configure connection string in <code>appsettings.json</code> 4. Register in DI: <code>builder.Services.AddDbContext&lt;MyDbContext&gt;()</code> 5. Inject in services</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-add-authentication","title":"Q: How do I add authentication?","text":"<p>A: 1. Install: <code>dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity</code> 2. Create User entity 3. Configure in <code>Program.cs</code> 4. Add login/logout pages 5. Protect routes with <code>[Authorize]</code></p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-add-email-sending","title":"Q: How do I add email sending?","text":"<p>A: 1. Create <code>IEmailService</code> interface 2. Implement with SMTP or SendGrid 3. Register in DI 4. Inject in components 5. Call <code>await emailService.SendAsync(...)</code></p> <p>See Code Patterns for examples.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-use-javascript-frameworks","title":"Q: Can I use JavaScript frameworks?","text":"<p>A: Blazor already handles interactivity. For extra JS: 1. Add files to <code>wwwroot/</code> 2. Reference in <code>_Host.cshtml</code> 3. Call from Blazor with <code>JS.InvokeAsync()</code></p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-debug","title":"Q: How do I debug?","text":"<p>A: - Visual Studio: Press F5 - VS Code: Open debug tab, select .NET - Rider: Press Ctrl+D</p> <p>Set breakpoints by clicking in margin.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-improve-performance","title":"Q: How do I improve performance?","text":"<p>A: 1. Build in Release mode: <code>dotnet build -c Release</code> 2. Enable tiered compilation 3. Profile with Visual Studio Profiler 4. Check logs for slow operations</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-handle-errors-better","title":"Q: How do I handle errors better?","text":"<p>A: Add custom exceptions and logging: <pre><code>throw new MyException(\"Detailed message\");\n_logger.LogError(LogEvents.MyEvent, ex, \"Error: {Error}\", ex.Message);\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#distribution","title":"Distribution","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-build-a-distribution","title":"Q: How do I build a distribution?","text":"<p>A: <pre><code>.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.05\"\n</code></pre></p> <p>Creates <code>ReportBuilder-v1.05.zip</code> ready to share.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-update-the-app-for-users","title":"Q: How do I update the app for users?","text":"<p>A: 1. Make code changes 2. Update version number 3. Build distribution: <code>.\\build-distribution.ps1 -Version \"1.05\"</code> 4. Distribute new ZIP to users 5. Users extract and run</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-can-i-customize-the-launcher","title":"Q: Can I customize the launcher?","text":"<p>A: Yes, edit <code>dist/ReportBuilder.bat</code> and <code>dist/Install.bat</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-do-i-host-the-documentation","title":"Q: How do I host the documentation?","text":"<p>A:  1. Build MkDocs: <code>mkdocs build</code> (creates <code>site/</code> folder) 2. Upload <code>site/</code> to web server 3. Users open in browser 4. Or generate PDF from MkDocs</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-how-big-is-the-download","title":"Q: How big is the download?","text":"<p>A: ~64 MB ZIP file (includes .NET runtime).</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-does-the-user-need-admin-rights","title":"Q: Does the user need admin rights?","text":"<p>A: No, unless they want to: - Create Start Menu shortcuts (optional) - Install to Program Files</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":""},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-port-5000-already-in-use","title":"Q: \"Port 5000 already in use\"","text":"<p>A: <pre><code>taskkill /F /IM dotnet.exe\ndotnet watch run\n</code></pre></p> <p>Or change port in <code>appsettings.json</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-connection-refused-in-browser","title":"Q: \"Connection refused\" in browser","text":"<p>A: 1. Wait 10-15 seconds (first start takes time) 2. Refresh browser 3. Check PowerShell for error messages</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-build-fails-with-errors","title":"Q: Build fails with errors","text":"<p>A: <pre><code>dotnet clean\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-hot-reload-not-working","title":"Q: Hot reload not working","text":"<p>A: Restart <code>dotnet watch run</code>.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-pdf-generation-very-slow","title":"Q: PDF generation very slow","text":"<p>A:  1. First generation is slower (compiling) 2. Subsequent ones are fast 3. Release build is faster: <code>dotnet build -c Release</code></p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-form-wont-validate","title":"Q: Form won't validate","text":"<p>A: Check browser console (F12) for JavaScript errors.</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#q-cant-import-pdf","title":"Q: Can't import PDF","text":"<p>A: 1. Verify PDF is from this app 2. Check PDF size &lt; 10 MB 3. Try simpler PDF first (fewer pages) 4. Check logs for error message</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#getting-help","title":"Getting Help","text":"<ol> <li>Check Documentation: Main docs</li> <li>Review Code: Code examples in source</li> <li>Check Logs: PowerShell output and browser console (F12)</li> <li>Search FAQ: Ctrl+F on this page</li> <li>Contact Developer: Create issue on GitHub</li> </ol>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#reporting-bugs","title":"Reporting Bugs","text":"<p>Include: - What you were doing - What went wrong - Error message (if any) - Operating system - App version</p>"},{"location":"reference/faq.html#feature-requests","title":"Feature Requests","text":"<p>Create issue with: - What feature you want - Why you need it - How it should work - Expected benefits</p> <p>Still stuck? Check Quick Start or Setup Guide.</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html","title":"Project Structure","text":"<p>Complete project folder organization.</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#root-directory","title":"Root Directory","text":"<pre><code>lehman.reports/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 Components/              # Blazor UI components\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 Config/                  # Configuration files\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 Models/                  # Data models\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 Services/                # Business logic\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 wwwroot/                 # Static assets\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 Properties/              # App properties\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 dist/                    # Distribution package\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc2 docs/                    # Documentation (MkDocs)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 Program.cs               # Application entry point\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 AppConstants.cs          # Configuration constants\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 ReportBuilder.sln        # Solution file\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 ReportBuilder.Web.csproj # Project file\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 build-distribution.ps1   # Distribution build script\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 mkdocs.yml               # MkDocs configuration\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 DOCUMENTATION.md         # Legacy (use MkDocs instead)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 LICENSE.md               # License file\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 .gitignore               # Git exclusions\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc4 .editorconfig            # (Moved to Config/)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#components","title":"Components/","text":"<p>Blazor UI components and pages.</p> <pre><code>Components/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 Pages/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Home.razor                  # Home page (/)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReport.razor       # Report form (/report)\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Error.razor                 # Error page\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 Layout/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 MainLayout.razor            # Main page layout\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 NavMenu.razor               # Navigation menu\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 MainLayout.razor.css        # Layout styles\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 NavMenu.razor.css           # Nav styles\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 Shared/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 ErrorDisplay.razor          # Error component\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 LoadingSpinner.razor        # Loading component\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 App.razor                       # Root component\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Routes.razor                    # URL routing\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 _Imports.razor                  # Imports for all components\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 _Host.cshtml                    # Host page HTML\n</code></pre> <p>Technology: Blazor Server, ASP.NET Razor</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#models","title":"Models/","text":"<p>Data models and JSON converters.</p> <pre><code>Models/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReportConfig.cs        # Report configuration\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MonthJsonConverter.cs           # Month serialization\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 AppSizeJsonConverter.cs         # App size formatting\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 [Custom models for new features]\n</code></pre> <p>Format: Plain C# classes, auto-properties</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#services","title":"Services/","text":"<p>Business logic and service interfaces.</p> <pre><code>Services/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 IReportGenerator.cs             # Report generation interface\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 MobileAppReportGenerator.cs    # Mobile app report PDF generation\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 PdfReportParser.cs              # PDF text extraction &amp; import\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ToastService.cs                 # Notification service\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Exceptions.cs                   # Custom exceptions\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 [Custom services]\n</code></pre> <p>Pattern: Interfaces + implementations, dependency injection</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#config","title":"Config/","text":"<p>Application configuration files.</p> <pre><code>Config/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.json                # Production settings\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.Development.json    # Development settings\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 .editorconfig                   # Code style rules\n</code></pre> <p>Format: JSON</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#wwwroot","title":"wwwroot/","text":"<p>Static files served to browser.</p> <pre><code>wwwroot/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 lib/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 bootstrap/                  # Bootstrap CSS/JS\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 jquery/                     # jQuery library\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 [other libraries]\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 index.html                      # Redirects to app\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 app.css                         # Custom styles\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 download.js                     # File download helper\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 favicon.png                     # Site icon\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 [other static files]\n</code></pre> <p>Served directly to browser, cached by browser</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#properties","title":"Properties/","text":"<p>Visual Studio project properties.</p> <pre><code>Properties/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 launchSettings.json             # Debug profile settings\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 AssemblyInfo.cs                 # Assembly metadata\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#dist","title":"dist/","text":"<p>Distribution package for end users.</p> <pre><code>dist/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 app/                         # Executable application\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 ReportBuilder.Web.exe       # Main executable\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 appsettings.json            # Production config\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 [.NET runtime files]        # ~50 MB of runtime\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ReportBuilder.bat               # Windows launcher script\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Install.bat                     # Create shortcuts script\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 README.md                       # User instructions\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 INSTALLATION.txt                # Setup guide\n</code></pre> <p>Generated by: <code>build-distribution.ps1</code> Used by: End users (no development needed)</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#docs","title":"docs/","text":"<p>MkDocs documentation source files.</p> <pre><code>docs/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 guides/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 quick-start.md              # 5-minute setup\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 installation.md             # Installation guide\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 first-report.md             # Creating first report\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 build-distribution.md       # Building distribution\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 deployment.md               # Deployment options\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 development/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 setup.md                    # Dev environment setup\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 architecture.md             # How app is structured\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 code-patterns.md            # Common patterns\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 adding-features.md          # Add new features\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 reference/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 project-structure.md        # (This file)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 api-reference.md            # Classes &amp; methods\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 configuration.md            # Config options\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 faq.md                      # Common questions\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 index.md                        # Home page\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 license.md                      # License info\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 site/                           # Generated HTML (git ignored)\n</code></pre> <p>Technology: MkDocs with Material theme View: Open <code>site/index.html</code> in browser after build</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#root-level-files","title":"Root Level Files","text":""},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#programcs","title":"Program.cs","text":"<p>Application startup and configuration: - Dependency injection setup - Middleware configuration - Service registration - Logging setup</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#appconstantscs","title":"AppConstants.cs","text":"<p>All application constants in one place: - Server URLs and ports - File size limits - Configuration values - Logging event IDs</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#reportbuildersln","title":"ReportBuilder.sln","text":"<p>Visual Studio solution file - contains project references.</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#reportbuilderwebcsproj","title":"ReportBuilder.Web.csproj","text":"<p>C# project file: - NuGet package references - Build configuration - Target framework (.NET 9.0)</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#build-distributionps1","title":"build-distribution.ps1","text":"<p>PowerShell script to build distribution: - Cleans previous builds - Restores packages - Publishes self-contained app - Creates ZIP archive</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#mkdocsyml","title":"mkdocs.yml","text":"<p>MkDocs configuration: - Site settings - Theme configuration - Documentation structure - Extensions</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#gitignore","title":".gitignore","text":"<p>Files excluded from version control: - bin/, obj/ (build output) - publish/ (release builds) - .vs/ (VS cache) - node_modules/ (if used)</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#editorconfig","title":".editorconfig","text":"<p>Code style rules (in Config/): - Indentation (4 spaces) - Line endings (CRLF) - Charset (UTF-8) - File types and rules</p>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#build-directories","title":"Build Directories","text":"<p>Generated during build (not in git):</p> <pre><code>bin/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Debug/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 net9.0/                    # Debug build output\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Release/\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 net9.0/                    # Release build output\n\nobj/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Debug/                         # Debug intermediate files\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 Release/                       # Release intermediate files\n\npublish/\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 net9.0/                        # Published self-contained app\n\nsite/                              # MkDocs generated HTML\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 index.html\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 css/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 js/\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 [other static files]\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#file-naming-conventions","title":"File Naming Conventions","text":"Type Convention Example Classes <code>PascalCase.cs</code> <code>MobileAppReportGenerator.cs</code> Interfaces <code>IPascalCase.cs</code> <code>IReportGenerator.cs</code> Components <code>PascalCase.razor</code> <code>Home.razor</code> Models <code>PascalCase.cs</code> <code>MobileAppReportConfig.cs</code> Styles <code>kebab-case.css</code> <code>main-layout.css</code> Scripts <code>kebab-case.js</code> <code>download.js</code> Documentation <code>kebab-case.md</code> <code>quick-start.md</code>"},{"location":"reference/project-structure.html#key-statistics","title":"Key Statistics","text":"Metric Value C# Files ~15 Blazor Components ~10 Documentation Files ~15 Total Packages ~2 (QuestPDF, iText7) Build Size (Debug) ~150 MB Build Size (Release) ~64 MB (ZIP) Lines of Code ~2000 <p>Next: Configuration Reference</p>"}]}